Schematic procedure for MIL-DLLME and back-extraction procedure

After extraction experiments, the sample solution was poured, and MIL loaded with metals (together with the stirring magnet to avoid any loss) remained in the glass tube. Then, 5 mL of 1 mol L−1 HNO3 was added for the re-extraction of metal species and they were mixed with a rotary mixer to ensure contact with the organic phase, even if adhered to the inner wall of the tube. The efficacy of back-extraction was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
