				\begin{document}$$Re-\text{extraction efficacy }\left(\%\right)=\frac{{V}_{\text{b}}\bullet {C}_{\text{b}}}{{V}_{\text{s}}\bullet \left({ C}_{\text{i}}-{C}_{\text{f}}\right)}\bullet 100$$\end{document}Re-extraction efficacy%=Vb∙CbVs∙Ci-Cf∙100where Vs is the sample volume, and Vb and Cb are the volume and metal concentration in the acidic solution used for back-extraction, respectively. Metal concentrations were measured by AAS.
